Le Nguyen Huu Duc is a Fresher Fullstack Developer with a strong foundation in academic and personal project development. Their core expertise encompasses **Cross-platform Development** using **Flutter/Dart**, applying the **MVC design pattern** for architectural robustness, and implementing **Agile/Scrum** methodologies. Duc has hands-on experience in building mobile applications, integrating **Firebase** for **authentication**, **real-time storage**, and **data synchronization**, notably optimizing data retrieval with **local caching** for up to 2x efficiency. They have also integrated **Google Cloud APIs** for address validation and **Google Maps API** for **location tracking** and delivery route visualization. Furthermore, Duc has conducted research into **Prompt Injection attacks** in **Large Language Models (LLMs)**, utilizing **Python** and the **Gemini API** to analyze attack vectors and evaluate mitigation strategies, demonstrating proficiency in **Prompt Engineering** concepts.
Technically, Duc is proficient across a broad spectrum of programming languages including **Dart, Python, Java, JavaScript, SQL, C/C++, C#, HTML/CSS**, and **GDScript**. Their framework and library experience includes **Flutter, Node.js, Google Maps API**, and **Gemini API**. For backend and cloud services, they are skilled with **Firebase** and **Google Cloud APIs**. Development tools utilized include **Git, Android Studio, VS Code**, and **Godot**. Key technical concepts and techniques mastered include **UI/UX Design, State Management, Error Reporting, Local Caching, Authentication, Real-time Storage, Location Tracking**, and **Cross-platform Development**. Duc also holds an **Agile & Scrum Framework** certification and demonstrates **Advanced English proficiency**, making them a well-rounded candidate for fullstack development roles.